    "Subsequently, predictions are made for each voxel center using a convolutional architecture.",
    "Previous methods voxelized the Fig. 13 Categorization of DL-based classification tasks for point cloudspoint clouds as dense grids; however, these methods were obstructed by the granularity of the voxels and the boundary artifacts due to the partitioning of the point cloud.",
    "In practice, there is no selection of a suitable grid resolution.",
    "To address these issues, advanced methods exploit the scalability of fully CNNs, allowing them to handle even large-scale point clouds [136].",
    "Moreover, these methods can train volumetric networks with different spatial sizes point clouds."
